<p>My question is similar to <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/7950338/cant-use-apostrophe-in-stringformat-of-a-xaml-binding%20this">this</a>: I'm working in Silverlight 4 and I'm trying to insert an apostrophe in a value that is bound to a TextBlock:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;TextBlock Text="{Binding MyValue, StringFormat='The value is &amp;apos;{0}&amp;apos;'}"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p>However, I'm getting XAML parse errors. I already tried escaping with <code>\'</code> and <code>&amp;quot;</code> but without success. Any ideas?</p>